After the fuse has been fitted, run the wire though the car to your amp. Since wires go to your trunk anyway (if that's where your amp is) find them with a repair manual and follow those with your new wires. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/80/Install-Sub-Woofers-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Install-Sub-Woofers-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/80/Install-Sub-Woofers-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Install-Sub-Woofers-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
